00:13:44,079 --> 00:13:46,957
So I'm gonna lay her down
in the back of my neighbor's van!

236
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:50,473
BERNADETTE:
All right, just hurry!

237
00:13:50,639 --> 00:13:55,110
Okay, I'll see you later, Ma--
Uh, lovely bride-to-be!

238
00:13:56,399 --> 00:13:58,515
I really gotta watch that.

239
00:14:04,279 --> 00:14:06,110
Come on, Raj, we're ready to start.

240
00:14:06,279 --> 00:14:09,396
We're ready when I say we're ready.

241
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:11,548
[MUTTERING]

242
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,199
Oop. Ahem.

243
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:16,397
Okay. Now we're ready.

244
00:14:16,560 --> 00:14:20,553
Ma, you wanna move your chair
over here so you can see?!

245
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:24,872
MRS. WOLOWITZ: I'm fine where I am!
I don't wanna fall off the roof!

246
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:29,551
You'll fall through the roof
before you fall off it.

247
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:32,559
Penny?

248
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:35,757
[VIVALDI'S "SPRING"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

249
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:40,237
Your new mother-in-law
is a piece of work.

250
00:14:40,560 --> 00:14:41,993
Not now, Dad.

251
00:14:42,159 --> 00:14:44,070
She's got a bigger mustache than me.

252
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:48,758
Here you go.

253
00:14:50,159 --> 00:14:52,992
Here you go? What am I, a football?

254
00:14:59,719 --> 00:15:02,631
Like that guy could catch a football.

255
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:07,398
"Howard and Bernadette,
the five of us stand before you...

256
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:10,358
...as your friends
and newly ordained ministers."

257
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:12,875
MRS. WOLOWITZ:
Louder!

258
00:15:13,999 --> 00:15:17,628
They all got ordained!
They're all marrying us! It's adorable!

259
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:19,756
If you wanna hear, come closer!

260
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:27,319
"Guys, when I look at the two of you
starting your lives together...

261
00:15:27,519 --> 00:15:30,158
...it fills my heart....

262
00:15:31,959 --> 00:15:34,427
[VOICE CRACKING]
It fills my heart...."

263
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,279
Okay, I'm gonna need a minute.

264
00:15:37,399 --> 00:15:39,230
Okay, I'll go. Ahem.

265
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:40,719
"Howard and Bernadette...

266
00:15:40,879 --> 00:15:44,076
...I know you two planned on getting
married in a big, fancy wedding.

267
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:47,710
When you're in love, it doesn't matter
where or how these things happen.

268
00:15:48,079 --> 00:15:51,116
ltjust matters
that you have each other."

269
00:15:51,679 --> 00:15:53,635
LEONARD:
Hmm.

270
00:15:55,439 --> 00:15:58,795
-Problem?
-No.

271
00:15:59,279 --> 00:16:03,113
I think the Reverend Hofstadter
is making an ironic connection...

272
00:16:03,279 --> 00:16:05,031
...between your statement
about love...

273
00:16:05,199 --> 00:16:08,236
...and your rejection of his proposal
in the bedroom.

274
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,469
Oh, grow up.

275
00:16:09,639 --> 00:16:11,470
-Hey, I didn't say it.
-That's enough.

276
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:13,830
-Well, he started it.
-Well, I'm ending it.

277
00:16:16,879 --> 00:16:21,873
"Bernadette, I wanna thank you for
allowing me to be your maid of honor.

278
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:25,511
I also want you to know
that I will be happy to do it again...

279
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:28,035
...if this marriage craps out."

280
00:16:33,639 --> 00:16:37,029
Thank you, Amy. Very touching.

281
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:40,232
"Howard and Bernadette...

282
00:16:40,399 --> 00:16:43,311
...you are lucky enough
to be best friends who love each other.

283
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:46,950
And that's the strongest kind of love,
because at its core...

284
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:51,318
...it has kindness, patience
and respect."

285
00:16:51,519 --> 00:16:55,478
Qualities that are hard to find
in people these days.

286
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:02,595
Would you like some aloe vera?

287
00:17:02,759 --> 00:17:04,556
You just got burned.

288
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:09,309
All right, my turn. Ahem.

289
00:17:09,479 --> 00:17:12,630
"Howard, Bernadette:"

290
00:17:13,479 --> 00:17:16,312
[SPEAKING IN KLINGON]

291
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:19,438
Sheldon, I told you, no Klingon.

292
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:26,152
Fine, I'll do it in English,
but it loses something.

293
00:17:28,039 --> 00:17:31,714
"The need to find another human being
to share one's life with...

294
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:33,518
...has always puzzled me.

295
00:17:35,279 --> 00:17:38,157
Maybe because I'm so interesting
all by myself.

296
00:17:39,799 --> 00:17:43,712
With that being said, may you find
as much happiness with each other...

297
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:46,474
...as I find on my own."

298
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:49,030
The Klingon would have made you cry.

299
00:17:51,039 --> 00:17:53,712
I believe you two have prepared vows?

300
00:17:57,799 --> 00:18:01,997
Howard Joel Wolowitz, like you,
this is going to be short and sweet.

301
00:18:04,199 --> 00:18:09,398
I love you with all my heart and soul
and promise to be with you forever.

302
00:18:13,839 --> 00:18:16,876
Bernadette Maryann Rostenkowski--

303
00:18:17,039 --> 00:18:18,757
MRS. WOLOWITZ:
Speak up!

304
00:18:18,919 --> 00:18:21,831
Hey, from now on, she's the only
woman who can yell at me!

305
00:18:26,319 --> 00:18:32,667
Until I met you, I couldn't imagine
spending my life with just one person.

306
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:40,075
And now I can't imagine spending
one day of it without you.

307
00:18:41,999 --> 00:18:46,117
ALL: By the power vested in us
by the state of California--

308
00:18:46,279 --> 00:18:47,598
And the Klingon High Council.

309
00:18:50,199 --> 00:18:54,670
ALL: --we now pronounce you
husband and wife.

310
00:19:13,879 --> 00:19:15,028
That's ignition.

311
00:19:15,199 --> 00:19:17,030
I love this part!

312
00:19:17,199 --> 00:19:18,632
Me too!

313
00:19:18,799 --> 00:19:21,836
l have strongly mixed feelings.

314
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:25,838
Oh, my God, it's happening.

315
00:19:26,319 --> 00:19:28,355
-Did I miss it?
-No, come on in. Hurry.

316
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:30,272
[MAN SPEAKING IN RUSSIAN
ON TV]

317
00:19:30,439 --> 00:19:32,794
I love that man.

318
00:19:32,959 --> 00:19:34,950
Me too.

319
00:19:39,039 --> 00:19:40,472
I can't believe it.

320
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:44,235
This whole time,
a small part of me thought he was lying.

321
00:19:49,559 --> 00:19:50,548
This is it.

322
00:19:51,079 --> 00:19:53,798
Boldly go, Howard Wolowitz.

323
00:19:53,959 --> 00:19:55,995
[MAN SPEAKING IN RUSSIAN
ON TV]

324
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:02,270
[HOWARD YELLING AND SOBBING]

325
00:20:27,439 --> 00:20:29,430
[English - US - SDH]

